	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jun 3rd 10:22 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.53]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Heh Heh. I knew you'd have something to say on this one Key, as I knew you wielded a CoT.&nbsp;&nbsp;Very good points, of course, and the other side of the argument.  Plus I underestimated the Baton/CoT crossover point (yes, that's the same table I use and should have checked it), but do note that in primary hand the CoT is only marginally better than the Baton well before crossover.<br><br>One other benefit to the EoD is the +5Dex, which is nice for getting your skills to fire a bit more, but the CoT is still obviously better off-hand if you don't mind the weight/cost trade-off.<br><br>I still think it's a a bad value, but then again I blow a ton of PP on tradeskills, so I try to save on equipment when I can do so without costing myself too much effectiveness (and 20% offhand is just not that much). <br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
