<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99167925785198></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99167925785198><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99167925785198>RE: Weapon for Low Lvl Monk</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99167925785198#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>502 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 4th 2:27 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.49]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>:)&nbsp;&nbsp;Ya caught me - I was thinking but forgot to mention that, while 2 CoTs are slightly better in damage output than baton/CoT, I wouldn't go for 2 CoT's not only because the combo's improvement over the baton/CoT is really small (as you noted) but also the baton's shorter delay will help with interrupting caster mobs - always a nice thing for us monks with our lousy resists.<br><br>My bottom line for the original poster - A baton has a place in every monk's life at some point, and my suggestion is that you save your nickels for one.  Osano is right - you'll get by fine through your teens on fists or (better yet) with a Sarnak Enforcer, but I remember feeling very under-powered in my teens (seems that Monks are weakest in high teens) and any advantage through that level range would be desirable IMO.<br><br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 44th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Strange Brew - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
